CommonFields.Title: Preparation and dielectric behaviors of thermoplastic and thermosetting polymer nanocomposite films containing BaTiO3 nanoparticles with different diameters
Author: Fan, Ben-Hui
Zha, Jun-Wei
Wang, Dong-Rui
Zhao, Jun
Zhang, Zhong-Feng
Dang, Zhi-Min
CommonFields.Location: Center of Dielectric Polymer Materials, School of Chemistry and Biological Engineering, University of Science and Technology Beijing, Beijing 100083, PR China

Additive.Additive: Barium hydroxide octahydrate (Xilong chemical Co. Ltd.)

Mixing.Description: BaTiO3 nanoparticles with different diameters were prepared by the alkoxide route.

BaTiO3 nanoparticles with different diameters were prepared by the alkoxide route.  The thickness for all as-prepared nanocomposite films were controlled in the thickness of about 100 um, and the BaTiO3 concentration at 50 vol %.

Scanning_Electron_Microscopy.Description: Crystal phase structures and morphologies of BT particles and nanocomposite films were characterized by a scanning electron microscope

Dielectric_and_Impedance_Spectroscopy_An.Description: For the measurment of the dielectric behavior, electrodes were painted by silver paste to ensure good electrical contact.  The dielectric properties of all films at -40 deg C, 20 deg C and 80 deg C were measured in the frequency range from 10^-2 Hz to 10^6 Hz using a precision impedance analyzer.

XRay_Diffraction_and_Scattering.Description: Crystal phase structures and morphologies of BT particles and nanocomposite films were characterized by an X-ray diffraction instrument.
